      "text": "[[Gem Stone]] is an [[Object Oriented Database]] that completely owns the execution runtime environment. Therefore, it is able to provide nearly transparent store and retrieve operations for objects in memory with transactional consistency.  For better or for worse, it provides application programmers the illusion of an infinite amount of persistent, transactional RAM.  Additionally, [[Gem Stone]] provides a query facility for stored objects and the ability to map objects to a relational database.",
